Mustardy Pork & Apples
1.
2.
Mustardy pork & apples
Method
Rub the pork steaks with a little oil and season with pepper and
salt to taste. Heat a large frying pan and fry the steaks for 2 mins on
both sides until golden. Transfer to a plate. Adding a little more oil
to the pan, fry the apples, onions and sage for 5 mins or until the
apples have softened.
Pour in the stock and spoon in the mustard, then return the pork
to the pan and simmer for 10 mins until the sauce has reduced by
about a third and the pork is cooked through. Serve with veg and
mashed potatoes.
